            <scopecontent>
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                                 <p>In this photocopy of a five-page typed letter, John J. Stevens of St. Louis, Mo., recalls coming to Middletown, Logan County, Ill., in 1847, and tells of Abraham Lincoln&#039;s 1853 christening of the town of Lincoln in that county. Stevens (b. 1840) wrote to Judge Lawrence B. Stringer, historian of Logan County. Stevens&#039; great-grandson, Rolland E. Stevens (b. 1915), of Urbana, Ill., gave the photocopied letter, and an outline of the family tree, to the Illinois Historical Survey about 1970.</p>
                        </scopecontent>
            


